<br>
Kigalan Wolfstar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uberedorsilverleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beredor Silverleaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arista's Taxi <br> Hides from Celi</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/02 10:00:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongbloodsong.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1194.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ2 Announced</span><hr size=1> Dunno bout the lag, but I definately agree about building space.  In UO, the game was out of space to place housing after a year or two, and the price of pre-placed housing flew, especially larger structures.  A tower, which cost 450k to get as a deed from a vendor, cost around 10-15 million if placed, last I played, and it most likely has risen.<br>
<br>
The local banks are cool, but could be annoying... if you forget where you put what, or just need to gather cash from like 5 banks just to buy something.  But we'll see. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125458"><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~briangeerlings/beredorsignature.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uaristasilverleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arista Silverleaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beredor's, Back Off!!</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/02 5:04:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongbloodsong.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1194.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ2 Announced</span><hr size=1> Sounds like it could be really neat, but there is only a little information on it right now and 3 or so pictures.  It's also a long ways off.<br>
<br>
It definatly sounds worth checking out for me.  I don't mind starting new games and leaving behind high level characters.  If the game is fun, then starting as a newbie is great because you have so much ahead of you that you haven't even touched yet.  Learning a game for the first time can be the funnest part.  I'd rather leave behind a char I've spent a lot of time on and do a new game if it means I have more fun...  I mean hey.. thats the point of these games.  The main thing I don't like about starting new games is losing the friends...  That'd be the main thing that I'd hate.  <br>
<br>
As for EQ2 itself... I think the bank localization could be either neat or a pain in the rear.  I like the idea that you could take a wagon and travel with all your stuff to another bank.  It also might keep players in one area a little more which means you see a lot of the same people a lot and make more friends.  But...  If you could lose your items trying to transfer them or if transporting them isn't fun in its self then I can see it sucking.  <br>
<br>
Housing in MMORPGs is sweet...  Always like it in Ultima Online and now i wanna see it in 3D... just hoping they fix the problem of land space some how.  <br>
<br>
Most of it sounded pretty neat though...  I'd like to see a griffon flying in the sky rather than floating above the ground and all the other graphics they mentioned.<br>
<br>
And... curious..  what stuff did they steal from daoc?  I've heard this twice, but every MMORPG is gonna steal something from another game.  Even EQ.  <br>
<br>
Also, they wont shut down EQ for EQ2. They will treat them as two different games... different teams.  They'll shut down EQ when its dieing down and too many people are quitting which will be many years.  <p>Arista Silverleaf<br>
