<br>
I think I like the idea of picking your class as you level but I haven't tried a game yet with that in it. So I dunno yet.  But I do like the idea of not twinking but thats cause my own style of play is closer to it.  I like the idea of earning my gear with each character and I like the idea of going out and fighting for my gear instead of just buying it.  But I've done plenty of twinking in EQ myself.  And I think it only makes it harder for those who've already worked up a character.  My first character was a druid who was in split paw armor at level 20 which I thought was cool at the time.  I had camped it with Celi's character in split paw and gotten it all myself (this wasn't long after the game was first released and the hardest stuff in split paw was 20's).<br>
<br>
We'll see though, this game is so far off I'm not even thinking about it for now.  But its neat to check out the awesome screenshots from time to time.  <br>
